JAPANESE ENCEPHALITIS AND OTHER - INDIA (14): (BIHAR)
*****************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 7 Sep 2011
Source: India Express [edited]
http://www.indianexpress.com/news/encephalitis-40-rise-in-cases-from-bihar-adds-to-states-agony/842929/


The state government, which is already struggling to handle the
increased number of acute encephalitis syndrome (AES) cases in eastern
Uttar Pradesh, now faces the fresh challenge of the acute rise in the
number of cases from Bihar. At BRD medical college in Gorakhpur, about
190 cases have already been reported from Bihar this year [2011].
Doctors at the hospital said the cases are mainly from Siwan and
Gopalganj districts of Bihar. Despite special measures taken by the
government this year like launching special sanitation campaigns to
counter the spread of the disease, about 15 percent rise in the number
of AES cases has already been reported this year in the state.

"About 1360 cases of AES have already been reported this year, out of
which about 190 cases are from Bihar. We get cases from Bihar and
Nepal each year but this year, the number of cases from Bihar has gone
up by 40 percent," said KP Kushwaha, senior doctor from BRD medical
college.

[Byline: Maulshree Seth]

